query.result:
115 Is he who, to have his neighbor suppressed, 116 hopes for excellence, and only for this desires 117 that he be put low in his greatness;
118 is he who power, grace, honor and fame 119 fears to lose because another surpasses, 120 so that he is saddened so that he loves the contrary;
121 and is he who for injury seems to offend, 122 so that he becomes greedy for revenge, 123 and such it is necessary that he imprint the evil of others.

127 Each one confusedly learns a good
